ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.324                Enzyme
NAME        7-deoxyloganetin glucosyltransferase;
            UDPglucose:iridoid glucosyltransferase;
            UGT6;
            UGT85A24
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-alpha-D-glucose:7-deoxyloganetin O-D-glucosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-alpha-D-glucose + 7-deoxyloganetin = UDP + 7-deoxyloganin
SUBSTRATE   UDP-alpha-D-glucose [CPD:C00029];
            7-deoxyloganetin
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            7-deoxyloganin [CPD:C06071]
COMMENT     Isolated from the plants Catharanthus roseus (Madagascar periwinkle) and Gardenia jasminoides (cape jasmine). With Gardenia it also acts on genipin. Involved in loganin and secologanin biosynthesis. Does not react with 7-deoxyloganetate. cf. EC 2.4.1.323 7-deoxyloganetic acid glucosyltransferase.
